Package gov.nasa.jpl.aerie.merlin.timeline

Class History<$Timeline>

java.lang.Object
gov.nasa.jpl.aerie.merlin.timeline.History<$Timeline>
Type Parameters:
$Timeline - The abstract type of the timeline owning this time point.
public final class History<$Timeline> extends Object
A view on prior events in a SimulationTimeline.

A History represents a point in time in a SimulationTimeline, tracking all of the events that have occurred before that point in time. Use a Query to interpret these events over time as knowledge in some domain.

New events can be emit(Event, gov.nasa.jpl.aerie.merlin.timeline.Query<? super $Timeline, Event, ?>)ted after any point in time, establishing a new point in time that observes the same timeline with a new event added at the end. Similarly, a duration of time may be await(gov.nasa.jpl.aerie.time.Duration)ed, producing a new point in time separated by the previous by the given span of time.

Histories may also be fork()ed, allowing timelines diverging from the same point in time to be rejoin(gov.nasa.jpl.aerie.merlin.timeline.History<$Timeline>)ed. The resulting join point is a point in time that observes the events on both branches.

See Also:
SimulationTimeline, Query
